# Styleguide Global Application

Use this rule whenever editing code in this repository.

## Core principle

Style conformance must never break or weaken code behavior.

## Mandatory execution protocol

1. Apply owner style rules as source of truth, including intentional owner-approved antipatterns.
2. Do not rely only on formatter output (`pint`, editor formatters, language defaults) to declare success.
3. Preserve semantics while refactoring style:
   - keep identifiers and contract keys exact;
   - keep route/method names exact;
   - keep assertion intent exact;
   - keep control-flow meaning exact.
4. Do not introduce speculative code changes outside the explicit style objective.
5. After edits, run a semantic verification pass in each changed file:
   - detect typo-level mutations (`$this` vs `this`, `->` vs `>`, wrong variable/key reference);
   - detect weakened checks (fallbacks that hide missing required data).
6. Validate both:
   - structural compliance (style/rule checks);
   - behavioral confidence (targeted tests/checks when applicable).
7. Completion is valid only when structural compliance is met and semantic drift is zero.

## Completion guardrail

If there is any doubt between "looks well formatted" and "matches owner style and behavior", choose owner style and behavior, then re-audit.
